    <centralBlocks>
      <Value><![CDATA[[
  {
    "key": "3c72b063-8b9c-4510-b27a-4d68e2d4fadd",
    "name": "What is a Graduate Apprenticeship?",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "What is a Graduate Apprenticeship? ",
    "content": "<p>Our Graduate Apprenticeship (GA) allows students to ‘work, earn and learn’ by studying for a degree when continuing in their employment.</p>\n<p>It is a practical and integrated way to launch a new career or develop expertise with their current employer.</p>\n<p>Employers will benefit as the Graduate Apprenticeship programme is an innovative, cost-effective way to attract and retain highly skilled, motivated and ambitious employees.</p>\n<p>More information regarding the Graduate Apprenticeship programme for employers can be found via <a rel=\"noopener\" href=\"https://www.apprenticeships.scot/for-employers/graduate-apprenticeships/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Skills Development Scotland GA Employers Guide\">Skills Development Scotland</a>.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "4b519cdf-3b61-4be3-8b8e-5c5e10e1f435",
    "name": "What are the benefits to employers?",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "What are the benefits to employers?",
    "content": "<p>There are many benefits to employers who enrol in QMU's Graduate Apprenticeship programme including:</p>\n<p><strong>No Fees</strong></p>\n<p>There are no additional costs for employers involved in the QMU Graduate Apprenticeship programme, all employers are expected to pay for is the employees standard salary - for more information on payment, please see 'Do Graduate Apprenticeships cost employers?'</p>\n<p><strong>Improved Recruitment &amp; Employee Retention</strong></p>\n<p>Employers linked with the Graduate Apprenticeship programme will have access to some of the most innovative and motivated employees available, working alongside QMU's academic staff with decades of experience at the top levels of business our students are motivated individuals with their finger on the pulse of modern business enterprise.</p>\n<p><strong>Increased Productivity &amp; Innovation</strong></p>\n<p>Our students will be learning in QMU's innovation focused Business School and applying their learning to your workplace, helping bring new skills and knowledge into your organisation.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "ecf8a434-e6aa-4a9a-bca5-e0ba81ac1eda",
    "name": "Do Graduate Apprenticeships cost employers?",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Do Graduate Apprenticeships cost employers?",
    "content": "<p>No, as an employer you will not incur any additional costs through being involved in the programme.</p>\n<p>Graduate apprentices are employees, so their employer will be expected to pay their salary.</p>\n<p>This salary is not set by Skills Development Scotland or Queen Margaret University but we do encourage all employers to pay the Living Wage. The employer will be expected to employ the apprentice full-time with full access to any facilities or benefits that you provide for other staff.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.apprenticeships.scot/help/full-list-of-faqs#employers\" title=\"Skills Development Scotland Employer FAQs\" data-anchor=\"#employers\">For more information on costs and salaries please see the Skills Development Scotland GA Guide.</a></p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "e2d0ebd7-3c3b-4c21-8b66-468976071bb3",
    "name": "Who can apply to work with QMU's Graduate Apprenticeship programme?",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Who can apply to work with QMU's Graduate Apprenticeship programme?",
    "content": "<p>There is no restriction on the size of organisation that can employ an Apprentice.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "652b3cb1-cf91-4240-8858-ebaf185cc38d",
    "name": "What is expected of employers involved in a Graduate Apprenticeship?",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "What is expected of employers involved in a Graduate Apprenticeship?",
    "content": "<p>Typically, the following would be expected of a Graduate Apprentice employer:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Meet with the learning provider, also known as the delivery partner (university/college/other provider) to agree the structure of the Graduate Apprentice programme. This includes assessment methods, time spent at university, and projects that will need to be supported in the workplace.</li>\n<li>Attend quarterly meetings with the delivery partner and the Graduate Apprentice, who is their employee.</li>\n<li>Mentor the Graduate Apprentice and get involved in training and assessment elements, as agreed with the learning provider.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Graduate Apprentices are new or existing employees of your business who are trained by colleges and universities. They'll spend around 80% of their time in work and 20% in training. It means the work and learning your apprentice does counts towards their qualification. </p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "de2d0c12-1783-459a-8928-5830297984e5",
    "name": "How do employers get involved?",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "How do employers get involved?",
    "content": "<p><strong>Register Your Interest</strong></p>\n<p>The first step in the Graduate Apprenticeship partnership is to express your interest in the programme and a member of the QMU team will contact you to arrange an initial meeting.</p>\n<p>Employers who are interested in a Graduate Apprenticeship partnership with Queen Margaret University should contact programme lead Mike Pretious via email at <strong><a href=\"mailto:mpretious@qmu.ac.uk\">mpretious@qmu.ac.uk</a> </strong></p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "d444f196-01a6-4cb7-a3d8-dada29601652",
    "name": "FAQs for employers",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "FAQs for employers",
    "content": "<p>Queen Margaret University is partnered with Skills Development Scotland in the delivery of our BA/Ba (Hons) Business Management (Graduate Apprenticeship) programme - a full FAQ's section on the process is available on the <a rel=\"noopener\" href=\"https://www.apprenticeships.scot/help/full-list-of-faqs#employers\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Skills Development Scotland\" data-anchor=\"#employers\">Skills Development Scotland website</a>.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "0891f279-2c4c-4b3c-a15c-f21d08f79f30",
    "name": "Queen Margaret University student testimonials",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Queen Margaret University student testimonials",
    "content": "<p>The Graduate Apprenticeships scheme has great benefits for employers as well as students.</p>\n<p>Hear what former student <a href=\"/study-here/student-stories/stuart-burnside-ba-hons-business-management-graduate-apprenticeship/\" title=\"Stuart Burnside Case Study\">Stuart Burnside</a> had to say about the programme and the impact it had one his personal and professional career.</p>\n<div class=\"mceNonEditable embeditem\" data-embed-url=\"https://youtu.be/QpSgPN676xY\" data-embed-height=\"1080\" data-embed-width=\"2249\" data-embed-constrain=\"true\"><iframe width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/QpSgPN676xY?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen=\"\" title=\"Stuart Burnside – BA (Hons) Business Management (Graduate Apprenticeship)\"></iframe></div>"
  },
  {
    "key": "de5cd1f4-5b0b-404e-8915-bec7de0d6566",
    "name": "Business Management Graduate Apprenticeship: Information Event",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Business Management Graduate Apprenticeship: Information Event",
    "content": "<p>Queen Margaret University (Edinburgh) invites employers in Scotland to a live webinar to discover more about our Graduate Apprenticeship degree in Business Management. Applications are now open for new students to start in September 2023.</p>\n<p>Graduate Apprenticeships are a work-based learning opportunity for current or new employees, allowing them to attain degree qualifications in the skills your business require. They broaden access to those wanting to take a different route to gaining a degree.</p>\n<p>In this session, you’ll find out how you can unlock professional development opportunities for your employees, and real benefits for your business.</p>\n<p>Key benefits to you, the employer:</p>\n<p>· Allows you to spot talented, motivated employees who would like, and are capable of development.</p>\n<p>· GA can be used to help recruit new staff and attract new talent into the business.</p>\n<p>· Learning costs are fully funded; there is no financial contribution required by you or the apprentice.</p>\n<p>· Graduate Apprentices work on real projects with your staff, bringing new ideas to those tasks and allowing mentors to build skills in developing others.</p>\n<p>Graduate Apprenticeships are open to employers of all sizes and sectors in Scotland, helping to build the skills your industry needs for the future.</p>\n<p>Graduate Apprenticeships are supported by Skills Development Scotland. Tuition fees are funded by Scottish Funding Council (SFC) and administered by Student Awards Agency Scotland (SAAS)</p>\n<p>This session will be run on Microsoft Teams. Prospective students for 2023 or 2024 start are also welcome. Contact ILO@qmu.ac.uk for GA information pack.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.ie/e/ba-hons-business-management-graduate-apprenticeship-information-event-tickets-647934007057\" title=\"Graduate Apprenticeships for Employers Eventbrite\"><strong>You can sign up for the event free of charge via Eventbrite.</strong></a></p>"
  }
]]]></Value>
